'''Timothy Chambers''' is a [[philosopher]] who has written a number of articles which have appeared in the journals ''Mind'' ([http://mind.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/reprint/109/434/195 2000], [http://mind.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/reprint/110/439/709 2001]), the ''Monist'' (1998), ''Philosophy'' (2001), the ''[http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/bpl/paso/2000/00000100/00000001/art00067 Aristotelian Society Proceedings]''(2000), and ''Ratio'' (1999).  His research interests include [[Hilary Putnam]], [[time travel]], the [[Ontological Argument]], the [[Doomsday Argument]] and the [[semantics]] of [[vagueness]].  His work on Putnam included a logical formula—the Chambers Conditional<ref>{{cite journal |last=Wright |first=C |title=On being in a quandary. Relativism vagueness logical revisionism  |journal=Mind |volume=110  |issue=437 |pages=45–98 |year=2001 |doi= 10.1093/mind/110.437.45 |url=http://mind.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/110/437/45 }}</ref>—which figures in [[Crispin Wright]]'s recent work on vagueness.<ref>[http://www.philosophy.ox.ac.uk/faculty/members/docs/inaugural.pdf]  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061006170748/http://www.philosophy.ox.ac.uk/faculty/members/docs/inaugural.pdf |date=October 6, 2006 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.st-andrews.ac.uk/philosophy/arche/pages/papers/Wright%20Liars%20and%20Heaps.pdf] {{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>

